  #------- FARMS -------#

  ### NEW BLOCK ###
  blocks {
    title: "Farms"
    description: "The number of farms and crop coverage are factors that influence food security by proxy. While they are not direct indicators of food insecurity, they are part of the broader agricultural landscape that contributes to food availability, affordability, and access. In some cases, farms may prioritize exporting crops over the cultivation of diverse and nutritious foods for local consumption. Prioritizing crop exports — and instead focusing on importing foods — can make local food systems vulnerable to global market fluctuations and global supply chain disruptions. Additionally, if the prices of imported foods increase, it can impact local economies and potentially hinder food affordability and access."
    columns {
      tiles {
        type: HIGHLIGHT
        description: "Farms in ${placeName}"
        stat_var_key: "Count_Farm"
      }
    }
